{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So how would you run a whole country without oil?"},{"time":4000,"text":"That's the question that sort of hit me"},{"time":6000,"text":"in the middle of a Davos afternoon about four years ago."},{"time":9000,"text":"It never left my brain."},{"time":11000,"text":"And I started playing with it more like a puzzle."},{"time":14000,"text":"The original thought I had: this must be ethanol."},{"time":16000,"text":"So I went out and researched ethanol,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and found out you need the Amazon in your backyard in every country."},{"time":21000,"text":"About six months later I figured out it must be hydrogen,"},{"time":24000,"text":"until some scientist told me the unfortunate truth,"},{"time":27000,"text":"which is, you actually use more"},{"time":30000,"text":"clean electrons than the ones you get"},{"time":32000,"text":"inside a car, if you use hydrogen."},{"time":34000,"text":"So that is not going to be the path to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"And then sort of through a process of"},{"time":40000,"text":"wandering around, I got to the thought"},{"time":42000,"text":"that actually if you could convert an entire country to electric cars,"},{"time":45000,"text":"in a way that is convenient and affordable,"},{"time":48000,"text":"you could get to a solution."},{"time":51000,"text":"Now I started this from a point of view that"},{"time":54000,"text":"it has to be something that scales en masse."},{"time":56000,"text":"Not how do you build one car,"},{"time":58000,"text":"but how do you scale this so that it can become"},{"time":60000,"text":"something that is used by 99 percent of the population?"},{"time":65000,"text":"The thought that came to mind is that it needs to be as good"},{"time":68000,"text":"as any car that you would have today."},{"time":70000,"text":"So one, it has to be more convenient than a car."},{"time":73000,"text":"And two, it has be more affordable than today's cars."},{"time":76000,"text":"Affordable is not a 40,000 dollar sedan, right?"},{"time":79000,"text":"Alright? That's not something that we can finance or buy today."},{"time":82000,"text":"And convenient is not something that you drive for an hour and charge for eight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"So we're bound with the laws of physics"},{"time":89000,"text":"and the laws of economics."},{"time":91000,"text":"And so the thought that I started with was"},{"time":94000,"text":"how do you do this, still within the boundary"},{"time":97000,"text":"of the science we know today --"},{"time":99000,"text":"no time for science fair, no time for playing around with things"},{"time":102000,"text":"or waiting for the magic battery to show up."},{"time":104000,"text":"How do you do it within the economics that we have today?"},{"time":106000,"text":"How do you do it from the power of the consumer up?"},{"time":108000,"text":"And not from the power of an edict down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"On a random visit to Tesla on some afternoon,"},{"time":114000,"text":"I actually found out that the answer comes"},{"time":116000,"text":"from separating between the car ownership"},{"time":119000,"text":"and the battery ownership."},{"time":121000,"text":"In a sense if you want to think about it this is the classic"},{"time":124000,"text":"\"batteries not included.\""},{"time":127000,"text":"Now if you separate between the two,"},{"time":129000,"text":"you could actually answer the need for a convenient car"},{"time":132000,"text":"by creating a network,"},{"time":134000,"text":"by creating a network before the cars show up."},{"time":137000,"text":"The network has two components in them."},{"time":140000,"text":"First component is you charge the car whenever you stop --"},{"time":143000,"text":"ends up that cars are these strange beasts that drive"},{"time":146000,"text":"for about two hours and park for about 22 hours."},{"time":149000,"text":"If you drive a car in the morning and drive it back in the afternoon"},{"time":153000,"text":"the ratio of charge to drive is about a minute for a minute."},{"time":156000,"text":"And so the first thought that came to mind is,"},{"time":158000,"text":"everywhere we park we have electric power."},{"time":161000,"text":"Now it sounds crazy. But in some places around the world,"},{"time":163000,"text":"like Scandinavia, you already have that."},{"time":166000,"text":"If you park your car and didn't plug in the heater,"},{"time":168000,"text":"when you come back you don't have a car. It just doesn't work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"Now that last mile,"},{"time":174000,"text":"last foot, in a sense,"},{"time":176000,"text":"is the first step of the infrastructure."},{"time":177000,"text":"The second step of the infrastructure needs to take care"},{"time":179000,"text":"of the range extension."},{"time":181000,"text":"See we're bound by today's technology on batteries,"},{"time":184000,"text":"which is about 120 miles if you want to stay within"},{"time":186000,"text":"reasonable space and weight limitations."},{"time":190000,"text":"120 miles is a good enough range for a lot of people."},{"time":194000,"text":"But you never want to get stuck."},{"time":196000,"text":"So what we added is a second element to our network,"},{"time":198000,"text":"which is a battery swap system."},{"time":200000,"text":"You drive. You take your depleted battery out."},{"time":203000,"text":"A full battery comes on. And you drive on."},{"time":206000,"text":"You don't do it as a human being. You do it as a machine."},{"time":208000,"text":"It looks like a car wash. You come into your car wash."},{"time":211000,"text":"And a plate comes up, holds your battery, takes it out, puts it back in, and"},{"time":214000,"text":"within two minutes you're back on the road"},{"time":216000,"text":"and you can go again."},{"time":219000,"text":"If you had charge spots everywhere,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and you had battery swap stations everywhere,"},{"time":223000,"text":"how often would you do it? And it ends up"},{"time":225000,"text":"that you'd do swapping less times than you stop at a gas station."},{"time":229000,"text":"As a matter of fact, we added to the contract."},{"time":232000,"text":"We said that if you stop to swap your battery more than 50 times a year"},{"time":235000,"text":"we start paying you money"},{"time":237000,"text":"because it's an inconvenience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239000,"text":"Then we looked at the question of the affordability."},{"time":242000,"text":"We looked at the question, what happens when the battery is"},{"time":244000,"text":"disconnected from the car."},{"time":246000,"text":"What is the cost of that battery?"},{"time":248000,"text":"Everybody tells us batteries are so expensive."},{"time":250000,"text":"What we found out, when you move from molecules to electrons,"},{"time":253000,"text":"something interesting happens."},{"time":255000,"text":"We can go back to the original economics of the car and look at it again."},{"time":258000,"text":"The battery is not the gas tank, in a sense."},{"time":260000,"text":"Remember in your car you have a gas tank."},{"time":262000,"text":"You have the crude oil."},{"time":264000,"text":"And you have refining and delivery of that crude oil"},{"time":266000,"text":"as what we call petrol or gasoline."},{"time":268000,"text":"The battery in this sense, is the crude oil."},{"time":272000,"text":"We have a battery bay. It costs the same hundred dollars"},{"time":275000,"text":"as the gas tank."},{"time":277000,"text":"But the crude oil is replaced with a battery."},{"time":279000,"text":"Just it doesn't burn. It consumes itself"},{"time":281000,"text":"step after step after step."},{"time":283000,"text":"It has 2,000 life cycles these days."},{"time":285000,"text":"And so it's sort of a mini well."},{"time":288000,"text":"We were asked in the past when we bought an electric car"},{"time":290000,"text":"to pay for the entire well, for the life of the car."},{"time":292000,"text":"Nobody wants to buy a mini well when they buy a car."},{"time":295000,"text":"In a sense what we've done is"},{"time":297000,"text":"we've created a new consumable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"You, today, buy gasoline miles."},{"time":301000,"text":"And we created electric miles."},{"time":304000,"text":"And the price of electric miles ends up being a very interesting number."},{"time":308000,"text":"Today 2010, in volume,"},{"time":310000,"text":"when we come to market, it is eight cents a mile."},{"time":314000,"text":"Those of you who have a hard time calculating what that means --"},{"time":316000,"text":"in the average consumer"},{"time":319000,"text":"environment we're in in the U.S."},{"time":321000,"text":"20 miles per gallon that's a buck 50, a buck 60 a gallon."},{"time":324000,"text":"That's cheaper than today's gasoline, even in the U.S."},{"time":328000,"text":"In Europe where taxes are in place,"},{"time":331000,"text":"that's the equivalent to a minus 60 dollar barrel."},{"time":336000,"text":"But e-miles follow Moore's Law."},{"time":340000,"text":"They go from eight cents a mile in 2010,"},{"time":343000,"text":"to four cents a mile in 2015,"},{"time":345000,"text":"to two cents a mile by 2020."},{"time":349000,"text":"Why? Because batteries life cycle improve --"},{"time":352000,"text":"a bit of improvement on energy density, which reduces the price."},{"time":355000,"text":"And these prices are actually with clean electrons."},{"time":358000,"text":"We do not use any electrons that come from coal."},{"time":362000,"text":"So in a sense this is"},{"time":364000,"text":"an absolute zero-carbon, zero-fossil fuel"},{"time":367000,"text":"electric mile at two cents a mile by 2020."},{"time":371000,"text":"Now even if we get to 40 miles per gallon"},{"time":373000,"text":"by 2020, which is our desire."},{"time":375000,"text":"Imagine only 40 miles per gallon cars would be on the road."},{"time":378000,"text":"That is an 80 cent gallon."},{"time":380000,"text":"An 80 cent gallon means, if the entire Pacific"},{"time":382000,"text":"would convert to crude oil,"},{"time":384000,"text":"and we'd let any oil company bring it out and refine it,"},{"time":387000,"text":"they still can't compete with two cents a mile."},{"time":391000,"text":"That's a new economic factor,"},{"time":393000,"text":"which is fascinating to most people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"Now this would have been a wonderful paper."},{"time":397000,"text":"That's how I solved it in my head. It was a white paper I handed out to governments."},{"time":400000,"text":"And some governments told me that it's fascinating"},{"time":402000,"text":"that the younger generation actually thinks about these things."},{"time":405000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":406000,"text":"Until I got to the"},{"time":408000,"text":"true young global leader, Shimon Peres, President of Israel,"},{"time":411000,"text":"and he ran a beautiful manipulation on me."},{"time":414000,"text":"First he let me go to the prime minister of the country,"},{"time":416000,"text":"who told me, if you can find the money you need for this network,"},{"time":418000,"text":"200 million dollars,"},{"time":420000,"text":"and if you can find a car company"},{"time":422000,"text":"that will build that car in mass volume,"},{"time":424000,"text":"in two million cars -- that's what we needed in Israel --"},{"time":426000,"text":"I'll give you country to invest the 200 million into."},{"time":430000,"text":"Peres thought that was a great idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433000,"text":"So we went out, and we looked at all the car companies."},{"time":437000,"text":"We sent letters to all the car companies."},{"time":439000,"text":"Three of them never showed up. One of them asked us"},{"time":441000,"text":"if we would stay with hybrids and they would give us a discount."},{"time":444000,"text":"But one of them Carlos Ghosn, CEO of Renault and Nissan,"},{"time":447000,"text":"when asked about hybrids said something very fascinating."},{"time":450000,"text":"He said hybrids are like mermaids."},{"time":452000,"text":"When you want a fish you get a woman and"},{"time":454000,"text":"when you need a woman you get a fish."},{"time":456000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":459000,"text":"And Ghosn came up and said,"},{"time":461000,"text":"\"I have the car, Mr. Peres; I will build you the cars.\""},{"time":463000,"text":"And actually true to form, Renault has put a billion and a half dollars"},{"time":466000,"text":"in building nine different types of cars that fit this kind of model"},{"time":469000,"text":"that will come into the market in mass volume --"},{"time":472000,"text":"mass volume being the first year, 100 thousand cars."},{"time":475000,"text":"It's the first mass-volume electric car,"},{"time":477000,"text":"zero-emission electric car in the market."},{"time":480000,"text":"I was running, as Chris said,"},{"time":484000,"text":"to be the CEO of a large software company called SAP"},{"time":487000,"text":"And then Peres said, \"Well won't you run this project?\""},{"time":491000,"text":"And I said, \"I'm ready for CEO\" And he said,"},{"time":493000,"text":"\"Oh no no no no no. You've got to explain to me,"},{"time":496000,"text":"what is more important than saving your country and saving the world,"},{"time":498000,"text":"that you would go and do?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":500000,"text":"And I had to quit and come and do this thing called A Better Place."},{"time":502000,"text":"We then decided to scale it up."},{"time":505000,"text":"We went to other countries. As I said we went to Denmark."},{"time":507000,"text":"And Denmark set this beautiful policy;"},{"time":509000,"text":"it's called the IQ test."},{"time":511000,"text":"It's inversely proportional to taxes."},{"time":513000,"text":"They put 180 percent tax on gasoline cars"},{"time":517000,"text":"and zero tax on zero-emission cars."},{"time":519000,"text":"So if you want to buy a gasoline car in Denmark, it costs you about 60,000 Euros."},{"time":523000,"text":"If you buy our car it's about 20,000 Euros."},{"time":525000,"text":"If you fail the IQ test they ask you to leave the country."},{"time":528000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"We then were sort of coined as the guys"},{"time":532000,"text":"who run only in small islands."},{"time":534000,"text":"I know most people don't think of Israel as a small island,"},{"time":536000,"text":"but Israel is an island -- it's a transportation island."},{"time":539000,"text":"If your car is driving outside Israel it's been stolen."},{"time":542000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":544000,"text":"If you're thinking about it in terms of islands,"},{"time":547000,"text":"we decided to go to the biggest island that we could find,"},{"time":549000,"text":"and that was Australia. The third country we announced was Australia."},{"time":552000,"text":"It's got three centers --"},{"time":554000,"text":"in Brisbane, in Melbourne, in Sydney --"},{"time":557000,"text":"and one freeway, one electric freeway that connects them."},{"time":559000,"text":"The next island"},{"time":561000,"text":"was not too hard to find, and that was Hawaii."},{"time":563000,"text":"We decided to come into the U.S."},{"time":565000,"text":"and pick the two best places --"},{"time":567000,"text":"the one where you didn't need any range extension."},{"time":569000,"text":"Hawaii you can drive around the island on one battery."},{"time":571000,"text":"And if you really have a long day you can switch,"},{"time":573000,"text":"and keep on driving around the island."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"The second one was the San Francisco Bay Area"},{"time":577000,"text":"where Gavin Newsom created a beautiful policy across all the mayors."},{"time":580000,"text":"He decided that he's going to take over"},{"time":582000,"text":"the state, unofficially, and then officially,"},{"time":585000,"text":"and then created this beautiful Region One policy."},{"time":589000,"text":"In the San Francisco Bay Area not only do you have"},{"time":591000,"text":"the highest concentration of Priuses,"},{"time":593000,"text":"but you also have the perfect range extender."},{"time":595000,"text":"It's called the other car."},{"time":597000,"text":"As we stared scaling it up"},{"time":600000,"text":"we looked at what is the problem to come up to the U.S.?"},{"time":603000,"text":"Why is this a big issue?"},{"time":605000,"text":"And the most fascinating thing we've learned is that,"},{"time":607000,"text":"when you have small problems on the individual level,"},{"time":610000,"text":"like the price of gasoline to drive every morning."},{"time":613000,"text":"You don't notice it, but when the aggregate comes up"},{"time":615000,"text":"you're dead. Alright?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":617000,"text":"So the price of oil, much like"},{"time":620000,"text":"lots of other curves that we've seen,"},{"time":622000,"text":"goes along a depletion curve."},{"time":624000,"text":"The foundation of this curve is that we keep losing the wells that are close to the ground."},{"time":627000,"text":"And we keep getting wells that are farther away from the ground."},{"time":630000,"text":"It becomes more and more and more expensive to dig them out."},{"time":632000,"text":"You think, well it's been up, it's been down,"},{"time":635000,"text":"its been up, it's going to keep on going up and down."},{"time":637000,"text":"Here is the problem:"},{"time":639000,"text":"at 147 dollars a barrel, which we were in six months ago,"},{"time":642000,"text":"the U.S. spent a ton of money to get oil."},{"time":646000,"text":"Then we lost our economy and we went back down to 47 --"},{"time":649000,"text":"sometimes it's 40, sometimes it's 50."},{"time":651000,"text":"Now we're running a stimulus package."},{"time":653000,"text":"It's called the trillion-dollar stimulus package."},{"time":655000,"text":"We're going to revive the economy. Hopefully it happens between now and 2015,"},{"time":659000,"text":"somewhere in that space."},{"time":661000,"text":"What happens when the economy recovers?"},{"time":664000,"text":"By 2015 we would have had at least 250 million new cars"},{"time":669000,"text":"even at the pace we're going at right now."},{"time":671000,"text":"That's another 30 percent demand on oil."},{"time":673000,"text":"That is another 25 million barrels a day."},{"time":676000,"text":"That's all the U.S. usage today."},{"time":680000,"text":"In other words at some point when we've recovered we go up to the peak."},{"time":683000,"text":"And then we do the OPEC stimulus package"},{"time":685000,"text":"also known as 200 dollars a barrel."},{"time":687000,"text":"We take our money and we give it away."},{"time":689000,"text":"You know what happens at that point?"},{"time":691000,"text":"We go back down. It's going to go up and down."},{"time":693000,"text":"And the downs are going to be much longer"},{"time":695000,"text":"and the ups are going to be much shorter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"And that's the difference between problems that are additive,"},{"time":700000,"text":"like CO2, which we go slowly up and then we tip,"},{"time":703000,"text":"and problems that are depletive,"},{"time":705000,"text":"in which we lose what we have,"},{"time":707000,"text":"which oscillate, and they oscillate until"},{"time":709000,"text":"we lose everything we've got."},{"time":713000,"text":"Now we actually looked at what the answer would be."},{"time":715000,"text":"Right? Remember in the campaign: one million"},{"time":717000,"text":"hybrid cars by 2015."},{"time":721000,"text":"That is 0.5 percent of the U.S. oil consumption."},{"time":725000,"text":"That is oh point oh well percent of the rest of the world."},{"time":730000,"text":"That won't do much difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732000,"text":"We looked at an MIT study:"},{"time":734000,"text":"ten million electric cars on the global roads."},{"time":737000,"text":"Ten million out of 500 million we will add between now and then."},{"time":741000,"text":"That is the most pessimistic number you can have."},{"time":743000,"text":"It's also the most optimistic number"},{"time":745000,"text":"because it means we will scale this industry"},{"time":748000,"text":"from 100 thousand cars is 2011,"},{"time":750000,"text":"to 10 million cars by 2016 --"},{"time":754000,"text":"100 x growth in less than five years."},{"time":759000,"text":"You have to remember that the world today is bringing in so many cars."},{"time":762000,"text":"We have 10 million cars by region."},{"time":765000,"text":"That's an enormous amount of cars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"China is adding those cars --"},{"time":769000,"text":"India, Russia, Brazil."},{"time":771000,"text":"We have all these regions."},{"time":773000,"text":"Europe has solved it. They just put a tax on gasoline."},{"time":775000,"text":"They'll be the first in line to get off"},{"time":777000,"text":"because their prices are high."},{"time":779000,"text":"China solves it by an edict. At some point they'll just declare"},{"time":781000,"text":"that no gasoline car will come into a city, and that will be it."},{"time":785000,"text":"The Indians don't even understand why we think of it as a problem"},{"time":788000,"text":"because most people in India fill two or three gallons every time."},{"time":790000,"text":"For them to get a battery that goes 120 miles"},{"time":793000,"text":"is an extension on range, not a reduction in range."},{"time":797000,"text":"We're the only ones who don't have the price set right."},{"time":800000,"text":"We don't have the industry set right."},{"time":802000,"text":"We don't have any incentive to go and resolve it"},{"time":804000,"text":"across the U.S."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"Now where is the car industry on that?"},{"time":808000,"text":"Very interesting. The car industry has been focused just on themselves."},{"time":811000,"text":"They basically looked at it and said, \"Car 1.0"},{"time":813000,"text":"we'll solve everything within the car itself.\""},{"time":817000,"text":"No infrastructure, no problem."},{"time":820000,"text":"We forgot about the entire chain around us."},{"time":823000,"text":"All this stuff that happens around."},{"time":825000,"text":"We are looking at the emergence of a car 2.0 --"},{"time":828000,"text":"a whole new market, a whole new business model."},{"time":831000,"text":"The business model in which the money that is actually coming in,"},{"time":834000,"text":"to drive the car --"},{"time":836000,"text":"the minutes, the miles if you want,"},{"time":838000,"text":"that you are all familiar with --"},{"time":840000,"text":"subsidize the price of the car,"},{"time":843000,"text":"just like cellphones. You'll pay for the miles."},{"time":845000,"text":"And some of it will go back to the car maker."},{"time":847000,"text":"Some of it will go back to your own pocket."},{"time":850000,"text":"But our cars are actually going to be cheaper than gasoline cars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853000,"text":"You're looking at a world where cars are matched with windmills."},{"time":857000,"text":"In Denmark, we will drive all the cars in Denmark"},{"time":860000,"text":"from windmills, not from oil."},{"time":863000,"text":"In Israel, we've asked to put a solar farm"},{"time":867000,"text":"in the south of Israel."},{"time":869000,"text":"And people said, \"Oh that's a very very large space that you're asking for.\""},{"time":872000,"text":"And we said, \"What if we had proven that in the same space"},{"time":874000,"text":"we found oil for the country for the next hundred years?\""},{"time":877000,"text":"And they said, \"We tried. There isn't any.\""},{"time":879000,"text":"We said, \"No no, but what if we prove it?\""},{"time":881000,"text":"And they said, \"Well you can dig.\" And we decided to dig up,"},{"time":883000,"text":"instead of digging down."},{"time":885000,"text":"These are perfect matches to one another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"Now all you need is about 10 percent"},{"time":891000,"text":"of the electricity generated."},{"time":893000,"text":"Think of it as a project that spans over about 10 years."},{"time":896000,"text":"That's one percent a year."},{"time":898000,"text":"Now when we're looking at solving big problems,"},{"time":901000,"text":"we need to start thinking in two numbers."},{"time":903000,"text":"And those are not 20 percent by 2020."},{"time":905000,"text":"The two numbers are zero -- as in zero footprint or zero oil --"},{"time":910000,"text":"and scale it infinity."},{"time":913000,"text":"And when we go to COP15 at the end of this year"},{"time":915000,"text":"we can't stop thinking of padding CO2."},{"time":917000,"text":"We have to start thinking about giving kickers to countries"},{"time":919000,"text":"that are willing to go to this kind of scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"One car emits four tons."},{"time":924000,"text":"And actually 700 and change million cars today"},{"time":926000,"text":"emit 2.8 billion tons of CO2."},{"time":929000,"text":"That's, in the additive, about 25 percent of our problem."},{"time":932000,"text":"Cars and trucks add up to about 25 percent of the world's CO2 emissions."},{"time":937000,"text":"We have to come and attack this problem"},{"time":939000,"text":"with a focus, with an effort that actually says,"},{"time":941000,"text":"we're going to go to zero before the world ends."},{"time":944000,"text":"I actually shared that with some legislators here in the U.S."},{"time":948000,"text":"I shared it with a gentleman called Bobby Kennedy Jr., who is one of my idols."},{"time":953000,"text":"I told him one of the reasons that"},{"time":955000,"text":"his uncle was remembered"},{"time":957000,"text":"is because he said we're going to send a man to the moon,"},{"time":960000,"text":"and we'll do it by the end of the decade."},{"time":962000,"text":"We didn't say we're going to send a man 20 percent to the moon."},{"time":965000,"text":"And there will be about a 20 percent chance we'll recover him."},{"time":968000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":971000,"text":"He actually shared with me another story, which is from about 200 years ago."},{"time":975000,"text":"200 years ago, in Parliament, in Great Britain,"},{"time":978000,"text":"there was a long argument"},{"time":980000,"text":"over economy versus morality."},{"time":982000,"text":"25 percent -- just like 25 percent emissions today comes from cars --"},{"time":986000,"text":"25 percent of their energy"},{"time":989000,"text":"for the entire industrial world in the U.K."},{"time":992000,"text":"came from a source of energy that was immoral:"},{"time":995000,"text":"human slaves."},{"time":997000,"text":"And there was an argument. Should we stop using slaves?"},{"time":1000000,"text":"And what would it do to our economy?"},{"time":1002000,"text":"And people said, \"Well we need to take time to do it."},{"time":1004000,"text":"Let's not do it immediately. Maybe we free the kids"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and keep the slaves."},{"time":1009000,"text":"And after a month of arguments they decided to stop slavery,"},{"time":1012000,"text":"and the industrial revolution started within less than one year."},{"time":1016000,"text":"And the U.K. had 100 years of economic growth."},{"time":1020000,"text":"We have to make the right moral decision."},{"time":1023000,"text":"We have to make it immediately."},{"time":1026000,"text":"We need to have presidential leadership"},{"time":1028000,"text":"just like we had in Israel that said we will end oil."},{"time":1032000,"text":"And we need to do it not within 20 years or 50 years,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"but within this presidential term"},{"time":1039000,"text":"because if we don't, we will lose our economy,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"right after we'd lost our morality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045000,"text":"Thank you all very much."},{"time":1047000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}